      • create

        public static <T> Lookup<T> create(Map<? extends Object,? extends T> map)
        Creates a lookup based on given map. This is equivalent to create(map, null).

        Please note that the created lookup uses a copy of the map passed to ensure the thread safety and performance. So subsequent change to the map doesn't affect the create lookup object.

        Type Parameters:
        T - type of the reference object to be looked up
        Parameters:
        map - the map to create the lookup
        Returns:
        an implementation of Lookup that is backed by given map

      • create

        public static <T> Lookup<T> create(Collection<? extends T> source,
                   String expression)
        Create a lookup for objects in the given collection indexed by the value computed from given expression.

        This is equivalent to from(source).notEmpty().by(expression).index().

        Type Parameters:
        T - type of the reference object to be looked up
        Parameters:
        source - a collection of source data that can be looked up.
        expression - the index expression that can compute the index value from the source data
        Returns:
        an implementation of Lookup indexed by the specified expression

      • create

        public static <T> Lookup<Lookup<T>> create(Collection<? extends T> source,
                           String expression1,
                           String expression2)
        Create a two level lookup for objects in the given collection indexed by the values computed from the given expressions.

        This is equivalent to from(source).notEmpty().by(expression1).by(expression2).index().

        Type Parameters:
        T - type of the reference object to be looked up
        Parameters:
        source - a collection of objects that can be looked up.
        expression1 - the first index expression
        expression2 - the second index expression
        Returns:
        an implementation of Lookup of Lookup indexed by the specified expressions in order

      • create

        public static <T> Lookup<T> create(@CheckForNull
                   T defaultValue,
                   Collection<? extends T> source,
                   String expression)
        Create a lookup for objects in the given collection indexed by the value computed from given expression. The created lookup has default value returned when Lookup.get(Object) cannot find a reference object.

        This is equivalent to from(source).notEmpty().defaultTo(defaultValue).by(expression).index().

        Type Parameters:
        T - type of the reference object to be looked up
        Parameters:
        defaultValue - the default value to be used if the lookup object is not found
        source - a collection of objects that can be looked up.
        expression - the index expression
        Returns:
        an implementation of Lookup indexed by the specified expression
